@node "iNSTALLATiON" "iNSTALLATiON"
@toc "main"
  -» iNSTALLATiON «-
 +------------------+
 Copy <ziPSTRIP.list>, <ziPSTRIP.wild> and <ziPsTRiP.config> to s:
 Copy <ziPstrip> to c:
 (BBS owners: copy ziPstrip_TEMPEST to c: as well)

@endnode

@node "uSAGE" "uSAGE"
@toc "main"
  -» uSAGE «-
 +-----------+
 ziPStrip <ziP-ARCHIVE>

 NOTE:  If you want to use ziPStrip with Dopus just make a new
        entry as an AmigaDOS command and type
        <c:ziPstrip {f}>
        (you may have selected another path!)

@endnode

@node "bBS uSAGE" "bBS uSAGE"
@toc "main"
  -» bBS uSAGE «-
 +---------------+
 There is a special version for Tempest called <ziPstrip_TEMPEST>.
 This one may be used with any other BBS-Program. If you write
 a script for another BBS-Program please send it to me.
 The BBS-Version has the same template as the normal version.

 Usage with Tempest : 1. just copy the file <Scripts/Strip_zip> to
                         <TEMPEST:Scripts/>
                         (Be careful the old file <Strip_zip> gets
                         lost)
                      2. copy ziPstrip_TEMPEST to <c:>
                         Copy <ziPSTRIP.list>, <ziPSTRIP.wild>
                         <ziPsTRiP.config> to <s:>
                         wELL dONE !!!

 If you want to use this program with a BBS-Program, contact me
 @{"(the Author)" link "tHE aUTHOR" 0} to get a special registered Version (for FREE !)
 I just want to know how many people use my program ;-) .
@endnode

@node "tHE bRAiNFiLES" "tHE bRAiNFiLES"
@toc "main"
  -» tHE bRAiNFiLES «-
 +--------------------+
 There are 2 brainfiles. One for wildcard and one normal stripping.
 You can edit the brainfiles to add new bbs-adds you want to strip,
 but ensure that there is no BLANK line in the brainfiles !! This
 would DELETE THE ENTIRE ARCHIVE, YOU HAVE BEEN WARNED !!!
 Put only one filename in each line and remember, it takes more 
 time to check the archives if you add lots of new names to the 
 brainfiles.
 THIS OPTION IS NOT CASE SENSITIVE !!!

 
 a) The normal Brainfile (<ziPSTRIP.list>):
 
  Examples: 1. you want to strip <xTassy.bbs> from an archive.
               right: add <xTassy.bbs> to ziPSTRIP.list
               right: add <XtAsSy.bBs> to ziPSTRIP.list
               wrong: add <xTassy.bbs#?> to ziPSTRIP.list
   
            2. there is an add like <spirit!of!soul/JU6.dunno.V13> in 
               the archive.
               So you just add <spirit!of!soul/JU6.dunno.V13> .
               
  The easiest way to get the correct names, is to list the zip-archive
  and then snap the full name and path of the file you want to strip.
 

 b) The wildcard stripfile (<ziPSTRIP.wild>):

  Examples: 1. you want to strip all files that end with <.displayme> 
               right: add <.displayme> to ziPSTRIP.wild 
               wrong: add <#?.displayme#?> to ziPSTRIP.wild
                      (the wildcards were added automatically,
                       in fact the stripper wont work correct if
                       you add them in the ziPSTRIP.wild-barinfile) 
            2. you want to kill all files in the directory 
               <spirit!of!soul>.
               right: add <spirit!of!soul> to ziPSTRIP.wild
               wrong: add <spirit!of!soul/#?> to ziPSTRIP.wild


 NOTE: You may use the brainfiles from IStrip, but you have to copy
       them and rename them into <ziPSTRIP.list> and <ziPSTRIP.wild>

@endnode

@node "tHE cONFiG fiLE" "tHE cONFiG fiLE"
@toc "main"
  -» tHE cONFiG fiLE «-
 +---------------------+
 Edit this file (<ziPsTRiP.config>) to add a zipfile comment 
 (ASCI or ANSI). Only the first line will be used. It should be 
 located in the <S:> directory, otherwise no comment will be added.
 If you only want to strip the zipfile comment, then just delete this 
 file.
 
 Examples : 1. you want to add a textfile called <BBS:adds/board.add>.
               right: edit the <ziPsTRiP.config> file and enter
                      <BBS:adds/board.add> (take a look at the example 
                      config file.
               wrong: enter <board.add> (you have to enter the FULL 
                      PATH !!!)



